Czech Stocks Drop for Second Day, Led by Erste Bank, New World

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-04-26T15:26:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/czech-equities-drop-for-second-day-led-by-komercni-erste-bank.html
The Czech Republic’s main equity
index retreated for a second day, led by  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)  and
 New World Resources NV (NWR) , the country’s biggest supplier of coal
to steelmakers.  The PX gauge of 15 stocks declined 0.3 percent to 1,248.40
at the 4:28 p.m. close in  Prague , adding to a 0.3 percent
retreat on April 22. The market was closed for a state holiday
yesterday.  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB) , the Czech unit of Societe Generale SA,
ended a four-day advance, sliding 0.4 percent to 4,239 koruna.
 CEZ AS (CEZ) , the country’s biggest power utility, gained 1 percent to
915 koruna, its highest close in 10 months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  